Figure 2.11 (Mexican hat connectivity)¶

Figure 2.11 : Schematic of Mexican-hat inhibition profile that drives activity bubble formation necessary for smooth map organization, as implemented by two types of connection

In [8]:
def gaussian(x, mean, sigma):
    return np.exp(-np.power(x - mean, 2.) / (2 * np.power(sigma, 2.)))

xs = np.linspace(-10,10,100)
s1 = 1; s2= 5 # Sigmas
exc_vals = [(x,gaussian(x,0,s1)) for x in xs]
inh_vals = [(x,-0.2*gaussian(x,0,s2)) for x in xs]
combined = [(x,e+i) for ((x,e),(_,i)) in 
            zip(exc_vals, inh_vals)]
In [9]:

spatial = hv.Ellipse(0,0,s2) * hv.Ellipse(0,0,s1)
spatial + hv.Curve(exc_vals) * hv.Curve(inh_vals) + hv.Curve(combined)

Figure 2.12 (GCAL settling)¶

Figure 2.12 : Activity bubbles in response to training patterns in the GCAL model at the start and end of development (20000 iterations)

Generating this figure requires Topographica.

In [10]:
import topo
from topo.submodel.gcal import ModelGCAL
from topo.analysis import Collector
from featuremapper.command import measure_sine_pref, measure_response
topo.sim.model = ModelGCAL(area=2.0)
topo.sim()

First set a couple of display options:

In [11]:
%opts Image (cmap='hot') [sublabel_format='' show_title=False xaxis=None yaxis=None]

Next define what we want to measure:

In [12]:
gcal = topo.sim.model.specification

c = Collector()

# Projection activities
c.Activity.LGNOnAfferent =  c.collect(gcal.projections.V1.LGNOnAfferent)
c.Activity.LGNOffAfferent = c.collect(gcal.projections.V1.LGNOffAfferent)

# Sheet activities
c.Activity.Retina =      c.collect(gcal.sheets.Retina)
c.Activity.V1 =          c.collect(gcal.sheets.V1)
# Connection fields
c.CFs.LGNOnAfferent =    c.collect(gcal.projections.V1.LGNOnAfferent, grid=True)
c.CFs.LGNOffAfferent =   c.collect(gcal.projections.V1.LGNOffAfferent,grid=True)

# OR preference measurement
c.collect(measure_sine_pref.instance(durations=[0.225], scale=1), apply_output_fns=False)

The measure_response command moves simulation time forward one unit to record activities and then resets it. Therefore to view the activities in the Retina and LGN sheets at the same time, we need to advance one iteration to generate the first row of Figure 2.12A:

In [16]:
%%opts Image (cmap='hot')

topo.sim.Retina[:] + topo.sim.LGNOn[:] + topo.sim.LGNOff[:]
